verbose_text: Exposure to chitin, which is associated with allergic responses, was shown to drive IL-33 and thymic stromal lymphopoietin (TSLP) from resident alveolar type II cells, inducing the IRF4-IL-9 module in ILC2s, highlighting a critical interaction between resident ILCs and structural cells.
evidence: chitin, which is associated with allergic responses, was shown to drive IL-33
